  "original_title": "Sri Lanka t-bond yields further down ; rupee guidance peg up",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka t-bond yields further down ; rupee guidance peg up",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Yields in Sri Lanka\u2019s risk free treasury bonds and bills came down on Friday while a guidance peg on interbank spot trading strengthened slightly, dealers said.",
        "The three months\u2019 bill closed at 27.00/ 28.00 percent Friday down from 27.25/ 28.00 percent on Thursday.",
        "The One-year bill closed at 28.00/29.00 percent, steady from the previous day.",
        "A bond maturing on 01.06.25 closed at 24.80/25.00 percent down from 24.75/25.00 percent at last closing.",
        "A bond maturing on 15.07.29 closed at 24.30/25.00 percent steady from previous close.",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions strengthened by 37 cents to 361.30 against the US dollar on July 22 from the previous 361.67, data showed on Friday.",
        "Commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 368.30 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 22, steady from July 21, data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.30 -359.00 rupees, also steady from the previous day. (Colombo/July 22/2022)"
      ],
